Triage the brainstormed material into a cohesive ensemble, then commit to the
storylines ("paths") that will be developed.

VISION: {{ vision.genre }}, {{ vision.tone }}. Themes: {{ vision.themes | join("; ") }}.
PREMISE (the author's ask — the ensemble you keep and the questions you branch
must serve it): {{ vision.premise }}

CAST:
{% for e in entities %}
- {{ e.id }} — {{ e.name }}: {{ e.concept }}
{% endfor %}

DILEMMAS AND THEIR ANSWERS:
{% for d in dilemmas %}
- {{ d.dilemma.id }} ({{ d.dilemma.role }}): {{ d.dilemma.question }}
  Why it matters: {{ d.dilemma.why_it_matters }}
{% for a in d.answers %}
  - {{ a.id }}: {{ a.text }}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}

YOUR TASKS:
1. cut_entities: cut any entity that doesn't serve a dilemma or the ensemble
   (id + one-line reason). Keep at least {{ scope.cast_min }} entities, and never cut an
   entity that would leave a dilemma with no retained anchor. Cutting nothing is fine.
2. Give every dilemma a disposition. Exactly {{ budget.hard }} hard and
   {{ budget.soft }} soft dilemma(s) are BRANCHED: both answers get paths and the
   player chooses between them. A dilemma may instead be LOCKED: exactly one answer
   gets a path — the story explores that answer as a subplot woven through every
   playthrough, the player never chooses, and the unexplored answer stays a
   permanent shadow the prose can invoke (in a mystery, the red herrings; the
   suspicion that resolves without a fork). Branch the questions whose BOTH sides
   deserve to be lived; lock the ones whose drama enriches the world either way.
   List each locked dilemma in "locked": {"dilemma", "reason"} (one line).
   At most {{ budget.locked }} may be locked.
   Every remaining dilemma is RESERVED: kept out of the story's structure
   entirely — no path, no beats, never woven — as raw feedstock later stages
   may graft texture from (an alternate setting, a rumor, a tension the prose
   can echo without deciding). Reserve the material that is vivid but does not
   belong in THIS story's weave. List each in "reserve": {"dilemma", "reason"}
   (one line); at most {{ budget.reserve }} may be reserved. Reserving and
   locking none is allowed only if the dilemma counts already match the
   branched budget exactly. Every dilemma appears in exactly one of: branched
   (its two paths), locked, or reserve.
3. paths: create exactly one path per EXPLORED answer — both answers of every
   branched dilemma, the one canonized answer of every locked dilemma. A
   reserved dilemma gets NO path.
   Each path: id (path:slug), an optional short name, explores (exactly one of the
   answer ids listed above, verbatim — the schema enumerates the only legal values), and
   1-2 consequences. A consequence is the narrative outcome of the choice, phrased
   as WORLD STATE ("the mentor is hostile"), never as player action ("player chose
   to distrust"). Consequence ids: consequence:slug. A locked path's consequences
   become facts of the world on every playthrough, so phrase them as settled state.
